---

<DocLayout title="Ricuci — JEF" lang="en">
  <h1>JEF — Janome</h1>
  <p class="docs-lede">
    The Janome / Elna / Kenmore format. Binary header with an offset table
    pointing to the coordinate blocks; colors via the Janome thread chart.
  </p>

  <h2>What it supports</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Trims</strong>: supported as a command in the stream.</li>
    <li><strong>Colors</strong>: written as threads; the writer snaps them to the Janome chart (<code>warn.COLOR_QUANTIZED</code>).</li>
    <li><strong>Hoop</strong>: JEF knows a few standard hoops (hoop code in the header).</li>
    <li><strong>Coordinates</strong>: signed 0.1 mm deltas, long-form/multiples.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>UI notes</h2>
  <blockquote>
    JEF: colors are matched to the nearest Janome threads.
  </blockquote>

  <h2>Recognizing</h2>
  <p>
    No reliable magic bytes; <code>registry.ts</code> resolves JEF by
    extension.
  </p>

  <p class="docs-prevnext">
    <a href={withBase('en/docs/formats/dst')}>← DST</a>
    <a href={withBase('en/docs/formats/vp3')}>VP3 →</a>
  </p>
</DocLayout>